Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String s = "47";
System.out.println(s + 3);
System.out.println(Integer.parseInt(s) + 3);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String a = "9";
String b = "4";
double result = Integer.parseInt(a) / Integer.parseInt(b);
System.out.println(result);
```

What happens when the following code is executed?

```java
Integer x = null;
int n = x;
System.out.println(n);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
ArrayList<Integer> scores = new ArrayList<Integer>();
scores.add(80);
scores.add(90);
scores.add(70);
int total = 0;
for (int s : scores) {
    total += s;
}
System.out.println(total / scores.size());
```

What is the value of `r` after the following code executes?

```java
Integer p = 12;
int q = p;
Integer r = q + 3;
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
ArrayList<Double> vals = new ArrayList<Double>();
String[] data = {"2.5", "3.0", "4.5"};
for (String t : data) {
    vals.add(Double.parseDouble(t));
}
double total = 0.0;
for (int i = 0; i < vals.size(); i++) {
    total += vals.get(i);
}
System.out.println((int)(total / vals.size()));
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
ArrayList<Integer> vals = new ArrayList<Integer>();
vals.add(3);
vals.add(7);
vals.add(2);
int result = 0;
for (int v : vals)
{
    if (v > result)
    {
        result = v;
    }
}
System.out.println(result);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
String[] tokens = {"-5", "-10", "-3"};
int max = Integer.MIN_VALUE;
for (String t : tokens)
{
    int val = Integer.parseInt(t);
    if (val > max)
    {
        max = val;
    }
}
System.out.println(max);
```

Determine the output of the following code:

```java
Integer x = new Integer(50);
Integer y = new Integer(50);
System.out.println(x == y);
System.out.println(x.equals(y));
```

Consider the following code segment.

```java
ArrayList<Integer> vals = new ArrayList<Integer>();
vals.add(4);
vals.add(Integer.parseInt("6"));

Integer x = vals.get(0);
int y = vals.get(1);
vals.set(0, y + x.intValue());

System.out.println(vals.get(0) + " " + vals.get(1));
```

What will be printed after the code is executed?
